.nh
.TH "KUBECONFIG-MANAGER" "1" "Jan 0001" "kubeconfig-manager" ""

.SH NAME
kcm-prune - List (and optionally remove) state entries whose kubeconfig is gone or whose topology changed


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBkcm prune [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Walks the state file and reports entries that no longer match an actual
kubeconfig on disk — either the file referenced by path_hint is missing,
or its current stable fingerprint differs from the entry's key (meaning
the kubeconfig was edited in a way that changed its logical topology).

.PP
Default is a dry run: prints the list and exits. Pass --yes to actually
remove the stale entries.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--dir\fP=""
	Kubeconfig directory to match path_hints against (default: ~/.kube)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for prune

.PP
\fB--yes\fP[=false]
	Actually remove the stale entries (default: dry-run)


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBkcm(1)\fP
